comments.body:
You can probably get away with having an empty PopupMenuEntry state that everyone uses except `CheckedPopupMenuItem`. Something like:

``` dart
class PopupMenuEntryState<T, U extends PopupMenuEntry<T>> extends State<U> {
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => config.build(context);
}
```

Then in PopupMenuEntry:

``` dart
  PopupMenuEntryState<T, PopupMenuEntry> createState() => new PopupMenuEntryState<T, PopupMenuEntry>();
```

Then all the build functions can stay on the components, no need for any states except CheckedPopupMenuItem, which would do:

``` dart
  _CheckedPopupMenuItemState<T> createState() => new _CheckedPopupMenuItemState<T>();
```

...and _CheckedPopupMenuItemState would be defined as:

``` dart
class _CheckedPopupMenuItemState<T> extends PopupMenuEntryState<T, CheckedPopupMenuItem<T>> { ... }
```

